§lWelcome to Realistic Unreality!§r

This is a Kitchen Sink-esque style modpack, with an emphasis on realism without the realism.

§lThe Lore:§r

You spent all night trying to put together a crappy modpack to no avail. Right as your patience is dwindling, you find a mod on 4chan that's supposed to fix an error. You add it, and try to load the modpack. Since it takes forever to load, you end up taking a nap...

When you awake, your house is gone. You're lying on gravel. The world around you is definitely still Earth, but much smaller, and a lot more cubic.

You come to the conclusion that Earth is now in Minecraft, and you are too. You're no stranger to the game, so you know the drill.

§lThe Credits:§r

This modpack was made for the OneShot Discord. You may still use this modpack for your own purposes.

Official downloads are on GitHub:
https://github.com/wistlyr/Realistic-Unreality

For support, please see the #realisticunreality channel on our Discord:
https://discord.gg/oneshot
It seems not only did Earth enter Minecraft, but various mods have joined the party too. Your standard tools definitely won't cut it. Better get looking into alternatives, namely, Tinker's Construct.

Why get wooden tools when you can get fancy flint tools? Flint will be your best friend for Tinker's Construct early game. Get some flint, and make some tool parts at a part builder. Assemble your new fancy tool at a tool station.
Sometimes you will have to refresh the quests.
In order to survive, you will need to get some proper food. Kill these animals.
Make a bed, to sleep away the night.

You're gonna need a place to hide from the nonexistent cops, and the monsters at night. You've played Minecraft before, you know what you need, get to it already, daylight's ticking away. (Warning, you need a WHITE bed due to stuffs.)
I hate the title too. Craft some Grout, about two stacks should be good.
Obtain cobblestone and make a furnace.
Hit that upgrade button on your poorly named item to upgrade it to actually usable bricks!
Get the rest of the parts needed to create a smeltery with those Seared Bricks.

betterquesting:10.name:8: "how do you hold the bucket??? wouldn't the clay be like super hot???"
betterquesting:10.desc:8: Fill your new smeltery with lava to smelt things.

To actually make tools with your smeltery, you'll need to drain your molten metals onto a cast. You can make casts by combining (or "alloying") aluminum and copper together inside the smeltery. Placing a stone part on a casting basin and pouring out aluminum brass will make a cast for that part.

You're surviving fairly well. You've even picked up on some other things going on, but at this point you want answers. You've probably been seeing these giant towers littering the place you've called home. They started to show up when this whole mess started, so what better place to look? Take down one, and perhaps you'll learn what to do next.
No Description

Fighting that Golem was a huge nightmare, but it was well worth it. Just before the tower collapsed, you found some valuable information. As you suspected, the world of Minecraft proper has leaked onto planet Earth and messed with the natural order. Even if it's irreversible, at least you can now do what you want. Where even is everyone else, anyway?

You now know how to get to the overworld of Minecraft. To do so, you'll need to construct a portal. The following note may help you:

"Create an end portal made out of stone bricks on the ground. Place poppies inside, and sneakily use bone meal on one of the poppies. If you do it right, everything will work."
You have successfully managed to make it to the Overworld! This is where all the modded stuff spawns.
A melter uses solid fuels to heat itself. Obtain some coal.
Oh, you want to make a melter? A melter is like a smeltery but has less capacity. Use those seared bricks to make these items for your melter.

To actually make tools with your smeltery, you'll need to drain your molten metals onto a cast. You can make casts by combining (or "alloying") aluminum and copper together inside the smeltery. Placing a stone part on a casting basin and pouring out aluminum brass will make a cast for that part.
Obtain a beehive.
Troll someone.
Give someone a chance cube. "I'm helping!"
So, you have chosen a side?
So, you have chosen a side then?
Barter with someone, get them to give you the item, then don't pay them and run off
Kill someone who has trolled another person.
Find and harvest a cactus. "Ooh, spiky!"
So, you've chosen a side then?
So, you've chosen a side then?
